Package graphics

Class GraphicElement

java.lang.Object
graphics.GraphicElement
All Implemented Interfaces:
Movable
Direct Known Subclasses:
RectangleGraphicElement, SpriteGraphicElement, SquareGraphicElement
public abstract class GraphicElement
extends java.lang.Object
implements Movable
The class representing Generic Graphic Elements (i.e. Objects that can be displayed/rendered on a PixelMatrix. The PixelMatrix reference gets passed into the render-Method of the class.

  • Constructor Details

    • GraphicElement

      public GraphicElement()
      Default constructor. Places the x/y coordinates of the GraphicElement at (0|0). The default color is black.

    • GraphicElement

      public GraphicElement​(int x, int y)
      Constructor that creates a GraphicElement at position x/y. The default color is black.

      y - the y coordinate of the GraphicElement

    • GraphicElement

    • GraphicElement

      public GraphicElement​(int x, int y, int speedX, int speedY, Color color)
      Constructor that creates a GraphicElement at position x/y and with a predefined speed.
      Parameters:
      x - the x coordinate of the GraphicElement
      y - the y coordinate of the GraphicElement
      speedX - the speed of the GraphicElement in x-direction
      speedY - the speed of the GraphicElement in y-direction
      color - the color of the GraphicElement (eventually the background color)

  • Method Details

    • update

      public void update()
      Method in which the internal parameters of the GraphicElement (i.e. position or any other parameters that are introduced by derived classes to define a shape) can be updated. The next rendering step (render) can then be be based on these new internal parameters.

    • render

      public abstract void render​(PixelMatrix matrix)
      Method to transfer the pixels (graphic representation) of GraphicElement the to PixelMatrix (i.e. the lumenaer Screen)
      Parameters:
      matrix - the pixel Matrix
